results.description: I’m crazy enough to waltz into a deer park at 3am just to be alone with these beauties. Over the years I’ve learnt a few tricks when it comes to stalking deer in the park. Persistence is key - they will keep running from you - but use the wind to your advantage to cover as much ground as possible. When you run against the wind, especially if the leaves of the trees are rustling, they won’t hear you coming!
